          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The absolute photofission cross section of 209Bi",
                " has been measured with monoenergetic gamma-radiation",
                " between 40 and 65 MeV photon energy. The experimental",
                " result was compared with the excitation function",
                " calculated on the basis of the statistical model.",
                " In order to reproduce the measured data on",
                " sigma(gamma,f), the (gamma,n) cross section must",
                " decrease with increasing photon energy faster than",
                " the experimental total (gamma,n) cross section. This",
                " behavior can possibly be explained by assumption",
                " that after photon absorption a compound nucleus",
                " is formed only for a small, with photon energy",
                " decreasing, fraction of all decays."
              ]
            }
          ],
